      "Remove the chicken, shred it with two forks, and return it to the pot.",
      "For the dumplings: whisk the flour and baking powder together, then stir in the milk and melted butter just until a soft, slightly sticky dough forms - don't overmix.",
      "Bring the broth back to a gentle simmer. Drop the dumpling dough by the spoonful directly into the simmering liquid.",
      "Cover and simmer 15-18 minutes without lifting the lid - the dumplings steam through this way and can turn gummy if you peek too often.",
      "Top with parsley before serving."
    ]
  }
]